The paper discusses models to reduce semantic complexity in distributed digital libraries, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the treatment of term vagueness and document re-ranking, which are common topics in the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes the use of controlled vocabularies and network analysis, which are relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories, respectively. Finally, the paper mentions the development of value-added services, which could be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
